"...So?" [l][r]
"That's it. There is no more research to be done. This is the end." [l][r]
I said this in a voice that mixed feelings of regret and a little relief. [l][r]
"What about Chito?" Mr. Ishii said over the phone in an unreadable voice. [l][r]
"He kept saying, 'I get it, thank you.'" [l][r]
"Then... is that okay?" [l][r]
"...I don't know. But I'm sure Chito thought about it in her own way and came to that conclusion." [l][r]
"I know that," says Ishii, who still seems reluctant to give up. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

