As soon as my wife, Ishii-san and I left Chito's hospital, we returned to the exhibition site. [l][r]
The vehicle was no longer there.[l][r]
Ishii-san shouted at me to stop messing around, and I was shocked and ran around. I grabbed the staff member I had asked before and questioned him again.
and [r]
The only response I got was, "It was definitely there until two hours ago." [l][r]
In other words, somewhere between the time we put Chito in the ambulance and leaving the venue and the time we returned, that conspicuous vehicle must have just disappeared. [l][r]
Of course, there is no way that the vehicles would move on their own without human intervention. Someone had to move them. Both when loading and unloading.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

